lead_paragraph: In remarks to the Economic Club of New York, the Federal Reserve chairwoman said she expected the domestic economy to improve this year.

headline.print_headline: Saying Fed Sees Better Days Ahead, Yellen Sets Patient Course on Rates
headline.main: Janet Yellen Says Fed Still Plans to Raise Interest Rates but Carefully

snippet: In remarks to the Economic Club of New York, the Federal Reserve chairwoman said she expected the domestic economy to improve this year.
abstract: Federal Reserve chairwoman Janet L Yellen says in remarks to Economic Club of New York that economy remains on track and that Fed will continue to pursue patient course toward higher interest rates; comments seem to indicate that no rate increase is likely in April.
